g2:Structure.g2:sa.DESCRIPTION: This structure must contain two values. remote-queue-event-type is a symbol that can be ADDITION, REMOVAL, INVALIDATE-STATE, ATTRIBUTE-UPDATE, or NEW-STATE. The remote-queue-event-list is the list of items to be updated. In the case of the event type ADDITION they are the items which have been added to the queue. If the event type is removal, they are the items which have been removed from the queue. For an attribute update, the event list will contain the items whose attribute has changed. In this case and additional structure attribute, the grl-attribute-name (a symbol) will also be included. Finally, if the remote-queue-event-type is INVALIDATE-STATE or NEW-STATE, the remote-queue-event-list will contain all the items contained in the queue.

See g2-event-object. The source for a remote-queue-event should be the underlying queue? Alternatively, each queue could have a separate manager so that the listener knows which queue has been changed indirectly
